modules.description: Provides functions to parse, generate, and manipulate Software Heritage identifiers, including encoding and decoding operations. Works with custom data types representing swhid structures, such as revision, directory, and content identifiers. Used to validate and transform identifiers during archive processing and metadata extraction.

Provides functions to construct and deconstruct identifiers for software heritage objects, including content, directory, snapshot, revision, and release types, using object IDs and qualifier lists. Works with object IDs as strings, object types as enumerated values, and identifiers composed of core data and qualifier lists. Used to generate structured identifiers for tracking files, revisions, and snapshots within a version-controlled system.
